case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances: On July 27, 2004 a work crew worker clearing brush from an overgrown vacant lot in the Dolomite area at the north corner of the intersection of Charles Street and Simmons Street found human bones at the north coroner of the property laying on top of the ground and underneath a privet hedge.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: Dark colored shirt brand "Maurice Malone", size XXL, with ironed on patches.  The following individual letter patches were recovered: D(1), M(4), R(1), S(1), T(1), and two sets of PO.  One pair of dark in color "Dickies", 36X32 pants.  Eight corroded coins, with no legible date, found in the left front pocket.  One pair of gray in color sweat pants.
case_footwear: One pair of brown boots, size 10 1/2. Dark in color socks.
case_jewelry: "Watch-it" watch with rectangular face and a band of silvery metal links was found around the left wrist.  One simple stud earring.  Nugget style ring, man's stock size 10 with probably neither gold nor silver, but of base metal construction.
dental: Dental information / charting is available and entered
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
